===Glyph origin===
{{Han etyl}}
{{Han compound|戊|丁|c1=s|c2=p|ls=psc}}. The phonetic component is not [[囗]] or [[口]], as folk etymology states. According to Ji Xusheng 季旭昇, its original meaning was "city walls", with a reference to something protected conveyed by the weapon. Its original meaning is preserved in [[城]].

===Etymology===
Cognate with {{och-l|盛|id=1|to hold with a receptacle}}, {{och-l|城|city wall; city}}, {{och-l|盛|id=2|abundant; flourishing}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}).

According to {{zh-ref|Bodman (1980)}}, cognate with {{cog|bo|གྱང||wall}}, {{cog|bo|འགེངས་པ||to fill}}, {{cog|bo|བཀང||to fill to the brim}}, {{cog|bo|སྐོང་བ||to fulfill}}.

